    <title><literal>UserEvent()</literal></title>

    <indexterm significance="preferred">
      <primary>Dialplan Applications</primary>

      <secondary><code>UserEvent()</code></secondary>
    </indexterm>

    <simpara>Sends an arbitrary event to the manager interface.</simpara>

    <synopsis><command>UserEvent(<replaceable>eventname</replaceable>[,<replaceable>body</replaceable>])</command></synopsis>

    <para>Sends an event of your choosing to the manager interface. The
    resulting event packet has the following format:<programlisting>Event: UserEvent <replaceable>eventname</replaceable>
Channel: <replaceable>channelname</replaceable>
Uniqueid: <replaceable>call-identifier</replaceable>
[<replaceable>body</replaceable>]</programlisting></para>

    <simpara>Additional lines in the form <code>fieldname: value</code> may be
    specified in the body. Multiple lines are separated with the
    "<code>|"</code> ('pipe') character (in older versions of Asterisk, with
    "<code>," or</code> "<code>^"</code>) getrennt.</simpara>

    <simpara>Returns 0.</simpara>

    <programlisting>exten =&gt; 123,1,UserEvent(Test,Note: I am calling ${XY} now.)
exten =&gt; 123,n,Dial(${XY})</programlisting>

